relationships.description: Wet well control system contains the pump control unit
Wet well control system contains the control display panel
Control system monitors and interacts with the wet well
Pump control unit controls and monitors submersible pumps
Each submersible pump is equipped with a moisture sensor
Pump control unit receives depth‐based state from the float switch
Pump control unit monitors access door sensor for unauthorized entry
Float switch determines the depth of liquid in the wet well
Control display panel provides indicator lights for various states
Control display panel includes a buzzer for audible alarms
The wet well control system controls multiple submersible pumps
The wet well control system includes a pump control unit
The float switch sets the state for each pump based on liquid depth
The access door sensor provides input to the wet well control system
The control display panel is part of the wet well control system
The wet well control system controls multiple indicator lights
The wet well control system controls the buzzer

domain_model.plantuml:
@startuml
class WetWellControlSystem {
  +monitorLiquidLevel()
  +reportLiquidLevel()
  +monitorPumpState()
  +reportPumpState()
  +activateVisualAlarm()
  +activateAudibleAlarm()
  +switchPumpOn(pump: SubmersiblePump)
  +switchPumpOff(pump: SubmersiblePump)
  +provideAutomatedOperation()
  +provideLocalManualOverrideOperation()
  +provideLocalObservationalOperation()
  +startPumpMotors()
  +stopPumpMotors()
  +trackMotorRunningState()
  +monitorUnauthorizedEntry()
  +monitorEnvironmentalConditions()
  +monitorPumpPhysicalCondition()
  +displayRealTimeOperationalParameters()
  +displayHistoricalOperationalParameters()
  +provideAlarmFeature()
  +manualOverrideSite()
  +automatedOperationSite()
  +equalizePumpRunTime()
}

class PumpControlUnit {
  +startSubmersiblePumpMotor(pump: SubmersiblePump)
  +stopSubmersiblePumpMotor(pump: SubmersiblePump)
  +trackMotorRunningState()
  +trackMotorAvailability()
  +handleUnavailableMotor(pump: SubmersiblePump)
  +setHighWaterLevelAlarm()
  +equalizePumpRunTimes()
  +notifyExcessMoisture(pump: SubmersiblePump)
  +notifyOverheat(pump: SubmersiblePump)
  +monitorPumpingSite()
  +recordRealTimeOperationalParameters()
  +recordHistoricalOperationalParameters()
  +provideAlarmFeature()
  +displayRealTimeParameters()
  +displayHistoricalParameters()
  +monitorProhibitedEntry()
  +monitorSealLeak()
}

class ControlDisplayPanel {
  -digitalDepth: float
  +displayRealTimeParameters()
  +displayHistoricalParameters()
  +enableIndicatorLights()
  +soundBuzzer()
}

class WetWell {
  -liquidLevel: float
}

class SubmersiblePump {
  -isRunning: boolean
  -isAvailable: boolean
}

class FloatSwitch {
  -leadPumpDepth: float
  -lagPumpDepth: float
  -allowableHighLiquidDepth: float
  +evaluateDepth(currentDepth: float)
}

class MoistureSensor {
  +detectSealFailure(): boolean
}

class AccessDoorSensor {
  -state: string
  +detectDoorState(): string
}

class LevelSwitch {
  +indicateStartCondition()
}

class IndicatorLight {
  -isEnabled: boolean
}

class Buzzer {
  +sound()
}

WetWellControlSystem *-- PumpControlUnit
WetWellControlSystem *-- ControlDisplayPanel
WetWellControlSystem --> WetWell
PumpControlUnit --> SubmersiblePump
SubmersiblePump *-- MoistureSensor
PumpControlUnit --> FloatSwitch
PumpControlUnit --> AccessDoorSensor
FloatSwitch --> WetWell
ControlDisplayPanel *-- IndicatorLight
ControlDisplayPanel *-- Buzzer
@enduml

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of liquid in the wet well.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify how or to whom the level is reported (e.g., display, log, external SCADA).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the reporting channel, format, update frequency, and recipients (e.g., “report liquid level every 5 seconds to the control display panel and log to historical database”).

issues.description: No acceptance criteria or threshold values are given to verify correct reporting.
issues.suggested_fix: Define performance criteria (e.g., latency <1s, resolution ±0.1 ft) and test cases.

issues.description: Missing details about monitoring frequency, reporting mechanisms, and units of measurement.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify 'The system shall monitor liquid level every 5 seconds with accuracy of ±0.1 feet and report levels in feet via digital display and data logging'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the state of each pump and whether it is currently running or not.

issues.description: Does not specify the reporting mechanism or format for pump state (e.g., indicator lights, logs, network message).
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify how pump state is presented (e.g., “update indicator lights and send SNMP trap on state change”).

issues.description: No timing or accuracy requirements are specified for monitoring and reporting pump state.
issues.suggested_fix: Add timing constraints (e.g., detect and report within 500ms of state change).

issues.description: The phrase 'state of each pump and whether it is currently running' is redundant - running status is part of pump state.
issues.suggested_fix: Revise to 'The control system shall monitor and report the operational state of each pump including running status, availability, and fault conditions'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for activating a visual and audible alarm when a hazardous condition exists.

issues.description: “Hazardous condition” is not defined—could be high water, seal failure, overheat, unauthorized entry, etc.
issues.suggested_fix: Enumerate hazardous conditions that trigger alarms (e.g., high wet well level > allowableHighLiquidDepth, pump overheat >90°C).

issues.description: No criteria given to verify alarm activation (e.g., alarm duration, volume, light intensity).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify alarm thresholds and performance requirements (e.g., buzzer ≥85dB at 1m, LED flash rate ≥1Hz).

issues.description: The requirement does not define what constitutes a 'hazardous condition'.
issues.suggested_fix: List specific hazardous conditions (e.g., high liquid level, pump seal failure, unauthorized entry).

issues.description: Does not define what constitutes a 'hazardous condition' or specify alarm duration/reset procedures.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific hazardous conditions such as 'high liquid level above 8 feet', 'pump seal failure', 'motor overheating above 80°C', and 'unauthorized access detected'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation.

issues.description: REQ-006 duplicates functionality described in REQ-017 with different wording.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge REQ-006 and REQ-017 into a single requirement with consistent terminology for automated operation.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify the scope or rules for automated operation.
issues.suggested_fix: Define the conditions and logic for automated operation (e.g., based on liquid level, pump states).

issues.description: Does not specify what aspects of operation are automated or how automation is controlled.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify 'The system shall automatically control pump operation based on liquid level thresholds without manual intervention'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation.

issues.description: REQ-007 overlaps with REQ-016 (“provide a manual override of the site”).
issues.suggested_fix: Consolidate into one requirement and clarify scope of manual override (which functions and interfaces are overridden).

issues.description: The requirement does not describe how manual override interacts with automated operation.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the priority of manual override (e.g., overrides automation until reset) and how it is triggered.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation.

issues.description: “Observational operation” is undefined—unclear what controls are enabled or restricted in this mode.
issues.suggested_fix: Define observational operation (e.g., read-only display mode without pump control).

issues.description: 'Observational operation' is unclear - what can be observed and through what interface?
issues.suggested_fix: Specify 'The system shall provide a read-only mode displaying real-time operational parameters without control capabilities'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the pumping site for unauthorized entry or trespass.

issues.description: Overlaps with REQ-030 (pump control unit monitors site) and duplicates REQ-033/REQ-036 (broken circuit detection).
issues.suggested_fix: Define clear division of responsibility: which component performs entry monitoring and unify duplicate requirements.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall display real time and historical operational parameters.

issues.description: REQ-014 overlaps with REQ-037 (pump control unit displays parameters) and is inconsistent with REQ-031 (records parameters).
issues.suggested_fix: Separate recording and display responsibilities and align wording across REQ-014, REQ-031, REQ-037.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide an alarm feature.

issues.description: REQ-015 is redundant with REQ-004, which already mandates visual and audible alarms.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove or merge REQ-015 into the detailed alarm requirement (REQ-004).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Level switches shall be used to indicate when pump motors should be started.

issues.description: Specifies start condition but not the stop condition or hysteresis to prevent rapid cycling.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify both on and off thresholds and include debounce/hysteresis details.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect occurrence of a pump motor seal leak. If a leak has been detected, both an audible and visible alarm should be activated.

issues.description: REQ-020 requires turning off the pump on seal failure, but REQ-034 only specifies alarm activation.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that pump shutdown is mandatory on seal failure and that alarms must accompany the shutoff.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The access door sensor is used to determine the state, either opened or closed, of the wet well access door.

issues.description: This reads as a design statement, not a functional requirement—does not specify what the system does with the door state.
issues.suggested_fix: Rephrase as a functional requirement, e.g., “When the access door opens, the system shall activate an alarm if not in maintenance mode.”

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation.

issues.description: The requirement is too vague and does not specify what specific safety measures or protections are expected.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the safety measures (e.g., alarms, automatic shutdowns, access controls) and the hazards they mitigate.

issues.description: The requirement is too vague - 'safety and protection' lacks specific measurable criteria and doesn't define what constitutes adequate safety measures.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify concrete safety measures such as 'The system shall prevent electrical shock hazards by maintaining IP67 rating' and 'The system shall prevent gas accumulation by monitoring methane levels below 10% LEL'

issues.description: The requirement cannot be verified as it lacks measurable acceptance criteria.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific safety standards and testing procedures that can be verified during acceptance testing.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching each submersible pump on or off in a timely fashion depending on the level of liquid within the wet well.

issues.description: The term 'timely fashion' is vague and could lead to inconsistent implementations.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify time thresholds or conditions for switching pumps (e.g., within 5 seconds of reaching a certain level).

issues.description: 'Timely fashion' is vague and doesn't specify liquid level thresholds for pump operation.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify 'The system shall switch pumps on/off within 2 seconds of liquid level reaching defined thresholds: lead pump at 4 feet, lag pump at 6 feet'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall start the pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.

issues.description: The terms 'running over' and 'runs dry' are not quantitatively defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify liquid level thresholds for starting/stopping pumps (e.g., start at 80% capacity, stop at 10%).

issues.description: Missing specific liquid level thresholds for 'running over' and 'runs dry' conditions.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific levels such as 'start pumps when level reaches 4 feet to prevent overflow at 8 feet, stop pumps when level drops to 1 foot to prevent dry running'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the physical condition of each pump for the existence of moisture and excessive temperatures.

issues.description: The terms 'excessive temperatures' and 'existence of moisture' are not quantified.
issues.suggested_fix: Define thresholds for excessive temperature (e.g., >70°C) and moisture (e.g., >5% humidity).

issues.description: Does not define threshold values for 'excessive temperatures' or moisture levels.
issues.suggested_fix: Define thresholds such as 'temperature exceeding 80°C' and 'moisture presence detected by sensor resistance change'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall equalize the run time between the pumps.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify how run time equalization should be achieved (e.g., round-robin, least runtime first).
issues.suggested_fix: Define the algorithm for equalizing run times (e.g., alternate pumps for each cycle).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry to the wet well through the access door by way of broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

issues.description: This requirement duplicates REQ-036, which also covers prohibited entry detection.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge REQ-033 and REQ-036 into a single requirement.

issues.description: Missing subject - unclear which component is responsible for monitoring.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify 'The access door sensor shall monitor and detect...'

issues.description: Uses 'prohibited entry' while REQ-011 uses 'unauthorized entry' for the same concept.
issues.suggested_fix: Use consistent terminology throughout requirements

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the lead pump depth, the float switch shall set a state which causes the first pump to turn on.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify how 'first pump' is determined (e.g., primary/secondary designation).
issues.suggested_fix: Define how pumps are ordered (e.g., primary pump is Pump A, secondary is Pump B).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The float switch is a mercury switch used to determine the depth of liquid within the wet well and set the on or off state for each pump.

issues.description: Mercury switches are environmentally hazardous and may not be suitable for modern implementations.
issues.suggested_fix: Consider alternative technologies (e.g., optical or magnetic float switches).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running.

issues.description: Uses 'motor' terminology while REQ-003 uses 'pump' for similar functionality.
issues.suggested_fix: Use consistent terminology throughout - either 'pump' or 'motor' or clarify the distinction

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the environmental conditions within the wet well.

issues.description: Does not specify which environmental conditions to monitor or acceptable ranges.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify conditions such as 'temperature (0-50°C), humidity (0-95%), and methane concentration (below 10% LEL)'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide a manual override of the site.

issues.description: Duplicates REQ-007 functionality.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-007 or clarify the distinction between 'manual override operation' and 'manual override of the site'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation of the site.

issues.description: Duplicates REQ-006 functionality.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-006 or clarify the distinction

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall start the submersible pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.

issues.description: Duplicates REQ-009 but assigns responsibility to pump control unit instead of wet well control system.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the distinction between system-level and unit-level responsibilities or merge the requirements

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control display panel shall have a digital depth of influent measured in feet.

issues.description: 'Have a digital depth' is unclear - should specify display functionality.
issues.suggested_fix: Revise to 'The control display panel shall display the current depth of influent digitally in feet'

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry by way of a broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

issues.description: Duplicates REQ-033 functionality.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-033 or remove duplicate

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for displaying real time and historical operational parameters.

issues.description: Conflicts with REQ-014 which assigns display responsibility to the wet well control system.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether the pump control unit or control display panel is responsible for displaying parameters

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for handling ventilation fan control in hazardous conditions
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall monitor methane gas concentrations in the wet well using the methane sensor. When methane levels exceed 25% of the Lower Explosive Limit (LEL), the system shall automatically activate the ventilation fan and trigger both visual and audible alarms. The ventilation fan shall remain active until methane levels drop below 10% LEL.
missing_requirements.rationale: The system context mentions that hazardous concentrations of flammable gases and vapors can exist in the wet well, and the ventilation fan must direct fresh air into the wet well. This is a critical safety requirement that is currently missing.

missing_requirements.description: Missing backup power system integration and power failure handling
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall automatically detect power failures and switch to backup power within 5 seconds. During backup power operation, the system shall maintain all critical monitoring and alarm functions, prioritize pump operations based on liquid level, and provide visual indication of backup power status on the control display panel.
missing_requirements.rationale: The external systems include a backup power system, but there is no requirement specifying how the system should handle power failures and switch to backup power.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for logging and reporting unauthorized access attempts
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall log all unauthorized access attempts and generate a report for maintenance personnel and regulatory agencies.
missing_requirements.rationale: While there are requirements for detecting unauthorized entry, there is no requirement for logging and reporting these events, which is crucial for security and compliance.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for methane level monitoring and alarm
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall monitor methane levels in the wet well and activate alarms if concentrations exceed safe thresholds.
missing_requirements.rationale: The system context mentions the presence of hazardous gases, and the domain model includes environmental conditions, but there is no specific requirement for methane monitoring.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for pump maintenance scheduling based on run time
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall schedule maintenance for pumps based on their accumulated run time to ensure equal wear and prevent failures.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model includes pump run time tracking, but there is no requirement for using this data to schedule maintenance, which is a common best practice.

missing_requirements.description: Missing system initialization and self-diagnostic requirements
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Upon system startup, the system shall perform self-diagnostics including sensor connectivity tests, pump availability checks, and alarm system verification. All diagnostic results shall be logged and displayed. The system shall not enter automated operation mode until all critical components pass diagnostics or operators acknowledge any failures.
missing_requirements.rationale: There are no requirements covering how the system should be initialized or shut down, which is essential for operational safety and reliability.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data retention and archival
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall retain historical operational parameters for a minimum of 90 days. Historical data shall include pump runtime, liquid levels, alarm events, and environmental conditions recorded at 15-minute intervals. Data older than 90 days shall be automatically archived or purged based on configuration settings.
missing_requirements.rationale: While there are requirements for recording real-time and historical data, there is no specification for how long data should be retained or archived.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for user authentication and authorization
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Access to manual override, configuration, and alarm-suppress functions shall require user authentication and role-based authorization; all access attempts and actions shall be logged with user identity and timestamp.
missing_requirements.rationale: The system context mentions security measures to prevent unauthorized access, but there is no specific requirement for user authentication and authorization.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system health monitoring and alerts
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall continuously monitor its own health and generate alerts for any detected issues.
missing_requirements.rationale: There is no requirement for the system to monitor its own health, which is important for ensuring continuous operation and early detection of issues.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for communication with external regulatory systems
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall periodically report operational data to external regulatory systems as required by EPA and DEP.
missing_requirements.rationale: The system context mentions compliance with regulatory requirements, but there is no requirement for reporting data to external regulatory systems.

missing_requirements.description: Missing specific temperature and moisture threshold definitions
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall define specific thresholds: pump motor temperature exceeding 85°C shall trigger overheating alarm and automatic shutdown; moisture sensor detecting >5% water ingress shall trigger seal failure alarm and pump shutdown. These thresholds shall be configurable by authorized maintenance personnel.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model includes temperature and moisture attributes for motors, and requirements mention 'excessive temperatures' and moisture detection, but no specific threshold values are defined, making implementation and testing impossible.

missing_requirements.description: Missing pump runtime calculation and reporting requirements
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall continuously track and record the cumulative runtime for each pump motor in hours and minutes. Runtime shall be calculated from motor start to stop events. The system shall display current runtime for each pump on the control display panel and reset runtime counters when equalization targets are met.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model includes Motor.runTime attribute and requirements mention equalizing run times, but no requirements exist for how runtime is calculated, displayed, or reset, which is necessary for proper pump equalization.

missing_requirements.description: Missing timing requirements for pump switching operations
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall switch pumps on or off within 10 seconds of liquid level threshold detection. Emergency pump activation during high liquid level alarms shall occur within 5 seconds. All pump switching operations shall be completed within 30 seconds to prevent wet well overflow or running dry.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-005 mentions switching pumps 'in a timely fashion' but provides no specific timing requirements, which is critical for preventing overflow or pump damage in a wastewater system.

missing_requirements.description: Missing access door monitoring and response requirements
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: When the access door is opened, the system shall log the event with timestamp, activate a visual indicator on the control panel, and optionally disable automatic pump operations based on configuration. The system shall track door open duration and trigger an alarm if the door remains open for more than 30 minutes.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model includes access door sensor with state attributes, and requirements mention monitoring unauthorized entry, but no specific requirements exist for what actions to take when the door is legitimately opened for maintenance.

missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The control display panel shall display liquid depth in feet using a single digital readout with precision to one decimal place. The display shall update every 5 seconds and include units of measurement.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model shows ControlDisplayPanel with both 'digitalDepth' and 'depthInFeet' attributes, suggesting redundancy. REQ-035 mentions digital depth but doesn't clarify the relationship between these attributes.

missing_requirements.description: Missing sensor failure detection and response requirements
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall detect sensor failures including float switch malfunction, moisture sensor disconnection, and access door sensor faults. Upon sensor failure detection, the system shall activate appropriate alarms, log the failure, and switch to safe operational mode using alternative sensors or manual control until repairs are completed.
missing_requirements.rationale: No requirements exist for handling sensor failures, which could lead to unsafe conditions or system failures. The system must be able to detect and respond to sensor malfunctions to ensure safe operation.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement covers the ability to perform secure remote firmware or software updates.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The wet well control system shall support remote firmware updates over a secure channel (e.g., TLS), verify update integrity before installation, and allow rollback to the previous version if the update fails.
missing_requirements.rationale: Maintainability of the control system over its lifecycle requires secure and reliable software update capability, which is not addressed.

domain_model_issues.description: Both 'LevelSwitch' and 'LevelSwitches' classes model the same functionality.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Remove 'LevelSwitches' and consolidate its responsibilities into 'LevelSwitch'.

domain_model_issues.description: There are two relationships between WetWellControlSystem and PumpControlUnit (composition and association).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Retain a single composition relationship to reflect ownership and remove the redundant association.

domain_model_issues.description: Two attributes represent the same concept (digital depth in feet).
Three attributes model door open/closed state redundantly with different names.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Use a single boolean 'isOpen' or an enum 'doorState'.

domain_model_issues.description: Both 'isRunning' and 'state' track the same running status.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Remove one attribute and standardize on 'isRunning'.

domain_model_issues.description: Multiple methods model the same functionality with different names.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Consolidate into a single method 'setOperationMode(mode: OperationMode)'.

domain_model_issues.description: No model element represents the system’s mode (Automated, Manual Override, Observational).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce an 'OperationMode' enumeration or class and a controller attribute to track the current mode.

domain_model_issues.description: Alarms are scattered as methods; no dedicated 'Alarm' class captures alarm type, state, timestamp, or severity.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Define an 'Alarm' class with attributes (type, active, timestamp) and associate it with sensors and actuators.

domain_model_issues.description: Environmental monitoring (REQ-012) is implemented as a method but no sensor class models pH, temperature, humidity, etc.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create an 'EnvironmentalSensor' class with relevant attributes and associate it with WetWellControlSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: Cannot specify which indicator to enable (pump running, seal failure, etc.)—no parameters or state setters exist.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add methods like 'setPumpRunningIndicator(on: boolean)' or parameterize 'enable(type: IndicatorType, on: boolean)'.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes to track system states (e.g., current operation mode: automated/manual).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'operationMode' (enum: Automated, Manual, Observational).

domain_model_issues.description: The direct association between WetWellControlSystem and SubmersiblePump is redundant; pumps should only be controlled via PumpControlUnit.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Remove the direct association; all pump interactions should go through PumpControlUnit.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes to track motor run times for equalization (REQ-018, REQ-026).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a 'runTimes' attribute (map/dictionary linking motors to their run durations).

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks a unique identifier (e.g., 'motorID') to distinguish between motors for equalization.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a 'motorID' attribute to support tracking individual motors.

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements REQ-013 and REQ-029 specify monitoring pump temperature for overheating, but no temperature sensor class exists in the model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add TemperatureSensor class with methods to detectOverheating() and getTemperature(), and establish relationships with SubmersiblePump and PumpControlUnit.

domain_model_issues.description: The class has 29 methods, indicating poor separation of concerns. Many methods duplicate functionality or belong in other classes.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Refactor by moving display-related methods to ControlDisplayPanel, pump control methods to PumpControlUnit, and removing duplicate methods.

domain_model_issues.description: While IndicatorLight and Buzzer classes exist, there's no coordinating alarm system class to manage different alarm conditions and states.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add AlarmSystem class to coordinate visual and audible alarms, manage alarm states, and handle alarm acknowledgment.

domain_model_issues.description: The FloatSwitch class lacks methods to get current liquid depth readings, which is essential for its primary function.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add methods like getCurrentDepth() and updateDepthReading() to support the depth monitoring functionality.

domain_model_issues.description: The relationship between SubmersiblePump and Motor is unclear in the context of the requirements that reference both pump and motor operations.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the relationship - typically a SubmersiblePump should contain/compose a Motor, and methods should be properly distributed between the classes.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall implement safety measures including emergency shutdowns, hazard monitoring, and protective barriers to ensure pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and public safety with 99.9% hazard prevention rate and emergency response within 2 seconds of hazard detection.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The original requirement is too vague about what constitutes 'safety and protection'. Specific measurable safety criteria, response times, and safety mechanisms need to be defined for proper implementation and testing.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of liquid in the wet well.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall continuously monitor liquid level in the wet well with ±0.1 feet accuracy and report level measurements every 5 seconds to the display panel and log to historical database.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing specific accuracy requirements, monitoring frequency, and reporting format/destination. These details are essential for proper system design and testing.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the state of each pump and whether it is currently running or not.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall monitor each pump's operational state (running/stopped/fault) with status updates every 2 seconds and report pump states via indicator lights, display panel, and system logs.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Lacks specific monitoring frequency, reporting methods, and what constitutes different pump states beyond running/not running.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for activating a visual and audible alarm when a hazardous condition exists.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall activate visual (LED indicators) and audible (85dB buzzer) alarms within 1 second when hazardous conditions occur (high liquid level, pump failure, unauthorized access, or motor overheating).
requirement_completeness.rationale: Needs to define what constitutes hazardous conditions, alarm specifications (brightness, sound level), and response time requirements.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching each submersible pump on or off in a timely fashion depending on the level of liquid within the wet well.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The control system shall switch submersible pumps on when liquid level reaches lead pump depth (X feet) and lag pump depth (Y feet), and switch off when level drops to stop depth (Z feet), with switching response time within 3 seconds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Lacks specific liquid level thresholds and quantified definition of 'timely fashion'. These parameters are critical for proper pump operation and preventing overflow/dry running.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation mode that automatically controls pump switching based on liquid levels, equalizes pump run times, and monitors system status without manual intervention.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Too vague about what 'automated operation' encompasses. Needs to specify which functions are automated and their behavior.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation allowing operators to manually start/stop individual pumps, disable automatic controls, and reset alarms via physical control panel switches.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Needs to specify which functions can be manually overridden and how the override is activated/deactivated.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation mode that displays real-time system status, liquid levels, pump states, and alarms without allowing control actions.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Unclear what 'observational operation' means. Needs to specify what can be observed and how this mode differs from normal operation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall start the pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall start pump motors when liquid level reaches high threshold (X feet) to prevent overflow and stop motors when level drops to low threshold (Y feet) to prevent dry running, with level-based switching response within 3 seconds.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Needs specific liquid level thresholds and response time requirements. The rationale is partially present but lacks quantifiable criteria.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The wet well control system shall continuously monitor and maintain current running status of each motor with status updates every 2 seconds and store status history for 30 days.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Lacks specifics on monitoring frequency, status storage duration, and how the tracking is implemented.

reasoning.domain_model: Domain model created using improved aggregation method to preserve unique elements from all models
reasoning.analysis:
Analysis aggregated using deepseek with specialized component processing:
- requirement_completeness: The requirement completeness assessments from OpenAI, DeepSeek, and Claude were identical in their analysis of each requirement. Therefore, the combined assessment preserves all unique insights by directly using the common analysis. The conservative approach to completeness scores was maintained by keeping the low scores (30.0) where all sources agreed on the significant missing elements. All identified missing elements and suggested improvements were included as they were consistent across all sources.
- requirement_issues: Used improved aggregation due to issues with deepseek response
- missing_requirements: The missing requirements from all three sources (openai, deepseek, claude) were identical in content, structure, and numbering. Therefore, the comprehensive list preserves all unique requirements exactly as they were provided, with no need for combination or modification. Each requirement was checked for uniqueness and completeness, and all were found to be consistent across sources.
- domain_model_issues: The combined list preserves all unique issues from each source analysis while merging similar issues with the most detailed information. For example, the duplicate 'LevelSwitches' class issue is kept from the first source with its detailed description and suggested fix. The redundant attributes in 'AccessDoorSensor' and 'SubmersiblePump' are combined from multiple sources to provide a comprehensive view. Issues related to missing classes like 'TemperatureSensor' and 'AlarmSystem' are included from all relevant sources. The severity levels are maintained as per the original sources, with 'MUST FIX' issues prioritized. The suggested fixes are consolidated to provide clear, actionable recommendations for each issue.
